		<div class="comment-body"><p>OhioPrepper:<br />
I agree with everything you have said with one exception.  If you keep bees and don&#8217;t harvest the honey it will NOT go to waste.  It will be good for a pretty indefinate amount of time.  </p>
<p>I did a cutout this spring.  It was an old house that was going to be burnt down.  The bees had been living in the house for approximatly 20 years.  We cut almost 6 five gallon buckets of honey-filled-comb out of the exterior stud walls.  I am certain that the surplus had been accumulated over several years.  If you have been around bees very long you know they don&#8217;t know what the word &#8220;waste&#8221; is.  <img src="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" />    We humans need to remember bees didn&#8217;t start making honey because we like it&#8230;..  They make it because they are smart enough to store food.  </p>
